  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best things to do in San Francisco?",
  "response": "San Francisco is a vibrant city with a rich history, diverse culture, and iconic landmarks. Here are some of the best things to do when visiting:\n\n### Iconic Landmarks\n1. **Golden Gate Bridge** \u2013 Walk, bike, or drive across this world-famous bridge and enjoy stunning views of the city and bay.\n2. **Alcatraz Island** \u2013 Take a ferry to the historic former prison and explore its fascinating history.\n3. **Fisherman\u2019s Wharf & Pier 39** \u2013 Enjoy seafood, street performers, and the sea lions at this bustling waterfront area.\n4. **Coit Tower** \u2013 Visit this art deco tower for panoramic views of the city and see the murals inside.\n\n### Cultural Experiences\n5. **Chinatown** \u2013 Explore the largest Chinatown outside of Asia, with its vibrant streets, shops, and restaurants.\n6. **The Mission District** \u2013 Discover murals, hip cafes, and a thriving food scene in this culturally rich neighborhood.\n6. **Museums** \u2013 Visit the **de Young Museum**, **SFMOMA (San Francisco Museum of Modern Art)**, or the **Exploratorium** for art, science, and interactive exhibits.\n\n### Parks & Nature\n8. **Golden Gate Park** \u2013 Wander through gardens, visit the **California Academy of Sciences**, or check out the **Japanese Tea Garden**.\n9. **Presidio** \u2013 Explore this former military post turned national park with trails, views, and the **Walt Disney Family Museum**.\n10. **Lands End** \u2013 Hike along coastal trails for breathtaking views of the Golden Gate Bridge and the Pacific Ocean.\n\n### Food & Drink\n11. **Eat at Local Spots** \u2013 Try sourdough bread at **Boudin Bakery**, Dim Sum in Chinatown, or tacos in the Mission District.\n12. **Ferry Building Marketplace** \u2013 Sample artisanal foods and local produce at this iconic food hall.\n13. **Craft Breweries & Cafes** \u2013 Explore the city\u2019s thriving coffee and beer scene.\n\n### Unique Experiences\n14. **Ride a Cable Car** \u2013 Experience this iconic mode of transportation and enjoy the city\u2019s hilly terrain.\n15. **Painted Ladies** \u2013 Admire the famous Victorian houses at Alamo Square.\n16. **Palace of Fine Arts** \u2013 Stroll around this beautiful structure and its tranquil lagoon.\n17. **North Beach** \u2013 Explore San Francisco\u2019s Little Italy with its cafes, bookstores, and nightlife.\n\n### Day Trips\n18. **Muir Woods** \u2013 Visit the towering redwoods just outside the city.\n19. **Napa Valley or Sonoma** \u2013 Take a wine-tasting tour in one of California\u2019s famous wine regions.\n20. **Sausalito** \u2013 Explore this charming waterfront town just across the Golden Gate Bridge.\n\nWhether you\u2019re into history, nature, food, or culture, San Francisco has something for everyone. Be sure to check seasonal events and plan ahead for popular attractions like Alcatraz and Muir Woods reservations!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
